  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-04 04:24 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] 8fcc short clears, BTC reclaims constructive but cross-asset bearish\n\n**Task:** Run fresh P1 copy intelligence after P4 cooled to MIXED slow / TREND fast but remained PM-gated, checking whether `8fcc` short conflict persists or BTC net breaks below the hard defensive line.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 6L/1S**, **ETH 2L/6S**, **SOL 1L/7S**.\n- Current top-book notional: BTC **+$19.22M net long**, ETH **-$13.68M net short**, SOL **-$7.47M net short**, HYPE **-$10.71M net short**, JTO **+$355 net long only**.\n- BTC improved from prior pass: **+$15.11M \u2192 +$19.22M**, reclaiming above **+$17M** bullish/rebuild and remaining well above **+$10M** hard defensive.\n- Critical conflict cleared: prior `anon-0x8fcc` BTC SHORT **$3.94M** is no longer reported in the tracked BTC book; BTC shorts are now only `anon-0xf5d8` at **$926.8K**.\n- BTC long book remains concentrated: `anon-0xecb6` LONG **$17.27M**, `anon-0x57dd` LONG **$2.29M**, `beatmaker1@proton.me` LONG **$350K**, plus small longs.\n- Cross-asset divergence remains severe: ETH **2L/6S / -$13.68M**, SOL **1L/7S / -$7.47M**, HYPE **3L/6S / -$10.71M**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-8fcc-short-clears-btc-reclaims-constructive-but-crossasset-bearish-2026-05-04-0424.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC hard-defensive risk has cleared again: net is back above **+$17M**, and the `8fcc` short conflict disappeared. However, BTC leadership is still heavily concentrated in `ecb6`; this is a constructive BTC book, not a broad risk-on book.\n\n**Decision:** Upgrade BTC P1 from **constructive/watch with 8fcc short conflict** to **constructive BTC reclaim, ecb6-concentrated**. Clear the `8fcc` short conflict for now. Keep hard defensive trigger at BTC net < **+$10M** or